  "text": "IF3 to inhibit 50S docking in this mutant (Fig. 2) , which effectively compensates for the loss of bridge interactions. In the presence of partial deletions, however, IF3 retains its ability to inhibit 50S docking, and bridge B2a, which normally promotes 70S formation, is missing. The loss of B2a without loss of IF3 antiassociation activity can explain the reduced amplitude observed. Our results underscore the importance of bridge B2a formation during subunit joining [CITATION_1] , which effectively drives the reaction of 70SIC formation forward in the presence of IF3.",
